net.vtst.ow.eclipse.less: An Eclipse module for LESS (http://lesscss.org)
(c) Vincent Simonet, 2011.  All rights reserved.


********************************************************************************
OVERVIEW

This plugin provides support for the LESS stylesheet language
(http://lesscss.org) in Eclipse.   Its main feature are:
* Syntax highlighting,
* Outline tree,
* Validation (duplicated properties and variables),
* Content assist (for property names and property expressions),
* Automatic cross-references (variables and mixins),
* Launch compilation with LESS compiler.


********************************************************************************
REQUIREMENTS

This Eclipse plugin requires:
* Eclipse Indigo
* XText 2.1.0 (http://www.eclipse.org/Xtext/)


********************************************************************************
KNOWN ISSUES

The following constructs of the LESS language are not (yet) supported:
- Media queries (media.less, http://www.w3.org/TR/css3-mediaqueries/)
- CSS3 selectors (css-3.less)
- CSS escapes (css-escapes.less)
- Empty property values (css.less)
- Special case of the font: property
(The file names in parenthesis are the names of the test files from LESS
distribution in which the limitation becomes visible).

The following features are not supported in the editor:
- Refactoring.

